The course introduces the chosen field and the possibilities related to that. During the course, a student should become a better learner on the university level, and become aware of the research and development options offered in the Institute of Physics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to introduce the newcomers to physics BSc programme to their chosen speciality and its possibilities. In general, the course aims to give an overview of the specific features of and methods used in the study process in the university.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of this course, the student is expected to: 1.	Be aware of the specific features of the physics education and the opportunities related to the field of specialization;   2.	Based on a personal preference, use different studying skills and the facilitating/enhancing methods to improve those to achieve the best results in his/her studies.
